{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm not at all a cook."},{"time":2000,"text":"So don't fear, this is not going to be a cooking demonstration."},{"time":5000,"text":"But I do want to talk to you about something"},{"time":7000,"text":"that I think is dear to all of us."},{"time":10000,"text":"And that is bread -- something which is as simple"},{"time":13000,"text":"as our basic, most fundamental human staple."},{"time":17000,"text":"And I think few of us spend the day"},{"time":20000,"text":"without eating bread in some form."},{"time":23000,"text":"Unless you're on one of these Californian low-carb diets,"},{"time":27000,"text":"bread is standard."},{"time":29000,"text":"Bread is not only standard in the Western diet."},{"time":31000,"text":"As I will show to you, it is actually"},{"time":33000,"text":"the mainstay of modern life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"So I'm going to bake bread for you."},{"time":38000,"text":"In the meantime I'm also talking to you,"},{"time":41000,"text":"so my life is going to be complicated. Bear with me."},{"time":44000,"text":"First of all, a little bit of audience participation."},{"time":48000,"text":"I have two loaves of bread here."},{"time":51000,"text":"One is a supermarket standard:"},{"time":54000,"text":"white bread, pre-packaged,"},{"time":56000,"text":"which I'm told is called a Wonderbread."},{"time":59000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":60000,"text":"I didn't know this word until I arrived."},{"time":62000,"text":"And this is more or less,"},{"time":65000,"text":"a whole-meal, handmade,"},{"time":67000,"text":"small-bakery loaf of bread."},{"time":69000,"text":"Here we go. I want to see a show of hands."},{"time":72000,"text":"Who prefers the whole-meal bread?"},{"time":77000,"text":"Okay let me do this differently. Is anybody preferring the Wonderbread at all?"},{"time":81000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":82000,"text":"I have two tentative male hands."},{"time":86000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"Okay, now the question is really,"},{"time":92000,"text":"why is this so?"},{"time":94000,"text":"And I think it is because"},{"time":96000,"text":"we feel that this kind of bread"},{"time":99000,"text":"really is about authenticity."},{"time":102000,"text":"It's about a traditional way of living."},{"time":105000,"text":"A way that is perhaps more real, more honest."},{"time":109000,"text":"This is an image from Tuscany, where we feel"},{"time":112000,"text":"agriculture is still about beauty."},{"time":114000,"text":"And life is really, too."},{"time":116000,"text":"And this is about good taste, good traditions."},{"time":120000,"text":"Why do we have this image?"},{"time":122000,"text":"Why do we feel that this is more true than this?"},{"time":127000,"text":"Well I think it has a lot to do with our history."},{"time":130000,"text":"In the 10,000 years since agriculture evolved,"},{"time":133000,"text":"most of our ancestors have actually been agriculturalists"},{"time":137000,"text":"or they were closely related to food production."},{"time":140000,"text":"And we have this mythical image"},{"time":142000,"text":"of how life was in rural areas in the past."},{"time":146000,"text":"Art has helped us to maintain that kind of image."},{"time":149000,"text":"It was a mythical past."},{"time":152000,"text":"Of course, the reality is quite different."},{"time":154000,"text":"These poor farmers"},{"time":156000,"text":"working the land by hand or with their animals,"},{"time":158000,"text":"had yield levels that are comparable"},{"time":161000,"text":"to the poorest farmers today in West Africa."},{"time":164000,"text":"But we have, somehow,"},{"time":166000,"text":"in the course of the last few centuries, or even decades,"},{"time":170000,"text":"started to cultivate an image of"},{"time":172000,"text":"a mythical, rural agricultural past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"It was only 200 years ago"},{"time":178000,"text":"that we had the advent of the Industrial Revolution."},{"time":181000,"text":"And while I'm starting to make some bread for you here,"},{"time":184000,"text":"it's very important to understand"},{"time":186000,"text":"what that revolution did to us."},{"time":189000,"text":"It brought us power. It brought us mechanization, fertilizers."},{"time":195000,"text":"And it actually drove up our yields."},{"time":197000,"text":"And even sort of horrible things, like picking beans by hand,"},{"time":201000,"text":"can now be done automatically."},{"time":204000,"text":"All that is a real, great improvement, as we shall see."},{"time":209000,"text":"Of course we also, particularly in the last decade,"},{"time":213000,"text":"managed to envelop the world"},{"time":215000,"text":"in a dense chain of supermarkets,"},{"time":218000,"text":"in a chain of global trade."},{"time":221000,"text":"And it means that you now eat products,"},{"time":223000,"text":"which can come from all around the world."},{"time":226000,"text":"That is the reality of our modern life."},{"time":229000,"text":"Now you may prefer this loaf of bread."},{"time":233000,"text":"Excuse my hands but this is how it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"But actually the real relevant bread,"},{"time":239000,"text":"historically, is this white Wonder loaf."},{"time":243000,"text":"And don't despise the white bread"},{"time":246000,"text":"because it really, I think,"},{"time":249000,"text":"symbolizes the fact that bread and food"},{"time":252000,"text":"have become plentiful and affordable to all."},{"time":256000,"text":"And that is a feat that we"},{"time":258000,"text":"are not really conscious of that much."},{"time":261000,"text":"But it has changed the world."},{"time":263000,"text":"This tiny bread that is tasteless in some ways"},{"time":266000,"text":"and has a lot of problems"},{"time":268000,"text":"has changed the world."},{"time":271000,"text":"So what is happening?"},{"time":273000,"text":"Well the best way to look at that is to do a tiny bit of simplistic statistics."},{"time":277000,"text":"With the advent of the Industrial Revolution"},{"time":280000,"text":"with modernization of agriculture"},{"time":282000,"text":"in the last few decades, since the 1960s,"},{"time":286000,"text":"food availability, per head, in this world,"},{"time":289000,"text":"has increased by 25 percent."},{"time":292000,"text":"And the world population in the meantime has doubled."},{"time":296000,"text":"That means that we have now more food available"},{"time":299000,"text":"than ever before in human history."},{"time":301000,"text":"And that is the result, directly,"},{"time":303000,"text":"of being so successful"},{"time":305000,"text":"at increasing the scale and volume of our production."},{"time":309000,"text":"And this is true, as you can see, for all countries,"},{"time":312000,"text":"including the so-called developing countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"What happened to our bread in the meantime?"},{"time":317000,"text":"As food became plentiful here,"},{"time":319000,"text":"it also meant that we were able to decrease"},{"time":321000,"text":"the number of people working in agriculture"},{"time":325000,"text":"to something like, on average, in the high income countries,"},{"time":329000,"text":"five percent or less of the population."},{"time":333000,"text":"In the U.S. only one percent of the people are actually farmers."},{"time":337000,"text":"And it frees us all up to do other things --"},{"time":340000,"text":"to sit at TED meetings and not to worry about our food."},{"time":343000,"text":"That is, historically, a really unique situation."},{"time":347000,"text":"Never before has the responsibility to feed the world"},{"time":351000,"text":"been in the hands of so few people."},{"time":353000,"text":"And never before have so many people"},{"time":356000,"text":"been oblivious of that fact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359000,"text":"So as food became more plentiful, bread became cheaper."},{"time":363000,"text":"And as it became cheaper, bread manufacturers decided to add in all kinds of things."},{"time":367000,"text":"We added in more sugar."},{"time":369000,"text":"We add in raisins and oil and milk"},{"time":375000,"text":"and all kinds of things to make bread,"},{"time":377000,"text":"from a simple food into kind of a support for calories."},{"time":382000,"text":"And today, bread now is associated with obesity,"},{"time":386000,"text":"which is very strange."},{"time":388000,"text":"It is the basic, most fundamental food"},{"time":390000,"text":"that we've had in the last ten thousand years."},{"time":393000,"text":"Wheat is the most important crop -- the first crop we domesticated"},{"time":397000,"text":"and the most important crop we still grow today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399000,"text":"But this is now this strange concoction"},{"time":402000,"text":"of high calories."},{"time":404000,"text":"And that's not only true in this country,"},{"time":407000,"text":"it is true all over the world."},{"time":409000,"text":"Bread has migrated to tropical countries,"},{"time":411000,"text":"where the middle classes now eat French rolls and hamburgers"},{"time":415000,"text":"and where the commuters"},{"time":418000,"text":"find bread much more handy to use"},{"time":420000,"text":"than rice or cassava."},{"time":422000,"text":"So bread has become from a main staple,"},{"time":426000,"text":"a source of calories"},{"time":428000,"text":"associated with obesity"},{"time":430000,"text":"and also a source of modernity,"},{"time":432000,"text":"of modern life."},{"time":434000,"text":"And the whiter the bread, in many countries, the better it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"So this is the story of bread as we know it now."},{"time":440000,"text":"But of course the price of mass production"},{"time":444000,"text":"has been that we moved large-scale."},{"time":447000,"text":"And large-scale has meant destruction of many of our landscapes,"},{"time":451000,"text":"destruction of biodiversity --"},{"time":453000,"text":"still a lonely emu here"},{"time":455000,"text":"in the Brazilian cerrado soybean fields."},{"time":458000,"text":"The costs have been tremendous --"},{"time":460000,"text":"water pollution, all the things you know about, destruction of our habitats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"What we need to do is to go back to understanding what our food is about."},{"time":469000,"text":"And this is where I have to query all of you."},{"time":471000,"text":"How many of you can actually tell wheat apart from other cereals?"},{"time":475000,"text":"How many of you actually can make a bread"},{"time":478000,"text":"in this way, without starting with a bread machine"},{"time":481000,"text":"or just some kind of packaged flavor?"},{"time":485000,"text":"Can you actually bake bread? Do you know how much a loaf of bread actually costs?"},{"time":489000,"text":"We have become very removed"},{"time":491000,"text":"from what our bread really is,"},{"time":493000,"text":"which, again, evolutionarily speaking,"},{"time":495000,"text":"is very strange."},{"time":497000,"text":"In fact not many of you know that"},{"time":499000,"text":"our bread, of course, was not a European invention."},{"time":501000,"text":"It was invented by farmers in Iraq"},{"time":503000,"text":"and Syria in particular."},{"time":505000,"text":"The tiny spike on the left to the center"},{"time":508000,"text":"is actually the forefather of wheat."},{"time":511000,"text":"This is where it all comes from,"},{"time":513000,"text":"and where these farmers who actually, ten thousand years ago,"},{"time":516000,"text":"put us on the road of bread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Now it is not surprising"},{"time":521000,"text":"that with this massification and large-scale production,"},{"time":524000,"text":"there is a counter-movement that emerged --"},{"time":526000,"text":"very much also here in California."},{"time":528000,"text":"The counter-movement says, \"Let's go back to this."},{"time":531000,"text":"Let's go back to traditional farming."},{"time":533000,"text":"Let's go back to small-scale, to farmers' markets,"},{"time":537000,"text":"small bakeries and all that.\" Wonderful."},{"time":540000,"text":"Don't we all agree? I certainly agree."},{"time":542000,"text":"I would love to go back to Tuscany"},{"time":544000,"text":"to this kind of traditional setting,"},{"time":546000,"text":"gastronomy, good food."},{"time":548000,"text":"But this is a fallacy."},{"time":550000,"text":"And the fallacy comes from idealizing"},{"time":553000,"text":"a past that we have forgotten about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556000,"text":"If we do this, if we want to stay with traditional small-scale farming"},{"time":560000,"text":"we are going, actually, to relegate"},{"time":563000,"text":"these poor farmers and their husbands --"},{"time":566000,"text":"among whom I have lived for many years,"},{"time":568000,"text":"working without electricity and water, to try to improve their food production --"},{"time":571000,"text":"we relegate them to poverty."},{"time":574000,"text":"What they want are implements"},{"time":576000,"text":"to increase their production:"},{"time":578000,"text":"something to fertilize the soil,"},{"time":580000,"text":"something to protect their crop and to bring it to a market."},{"time":583000,"text":"We cannot just think that small-scale"},{"time":585000,"text":"is the solution to the world food problem."},{"time":588000,"text":"It's a luxury solution for us who can afford it,"},{"time":591000,"text":"if you want to afford it."},{"time":593000,"text":"In fact we do not want this poor woman"},{"time":595000,"text":"to work the land like this."},{"time":597000,"text":"If we say just small-scale production,"},{"time":599000,"text":"as is the tendency here,"},{"time":601000,"text":"to go back to local food means that a poor man like Hans Rosling"},{"time":604000,"text":"cannot even eat oranges anymore"},{"time":606000,"text":"because in Scandinavia we don't have oranges."},{"time":609000,"text":"So local food production is out."},{"time":611000,"text":"But also we do not want"},{"time":613000,"text":"to relegate to poverty in the rural areas."},{"time":616000,"text":"And we do not want to relegate"},{"time":618000,"text":"the urban poor to starvation."},{"time":621000,"text":"So we must find other solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"One of our problems is that world food production"},{"time":626000,"text":"needs to increase very rapidly --"},{"time":628000,"text":"doubling by about 2030."},{"time":631000,"text":"The main driver of that is actually meat."},{"time":634000,"text":"And meat consumption in Southeast Asia and China in particular"},{"time":637000,"text":"is what drives the prices of cereals."},{"time":642000,"text":"That need for animal protein is going to continue."},{"time":646000,"text":"We can discuss alternatives in another talk, perhaps one day,"},{"time":649000,"text":"but this is our driving force."},{"time":651000,"text":"So what can we do?"},{"time":653000,"text":"Can we find a solution to produce more?"},{"time":657000,"text":"Yes. But we need mechanization."},{"time":661000,"text":"And I'm making a real plea here."},{"time":663000,"text":"I feel so strongly that you cannot ask a small farmer"},{"time":667000,"text":"to work the land and bend over to grow a hectare of rice,"},{"time":670000,"text":"150,000 times, just to plant a crop and weed it."},{"time":674000,"text":"You cannot ask people to work under these conditions."},{"time":677000,"text":"We need clever low-key mechanization"},{"time":680000,"text":"that avoids the problems of the large-scale mechanization that we've had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"So what can we do?"},{"time":686000,"text":"We must feed three billion people in cities."},{"time":689000,"text":"We will not do that through small farmers' markets"},{"time":691000,"text":"because these people have no small farmers' markets at their disposal."},{"time":695000,"text":"They have low incomes. And they benefit"},{"time":698000,"text":"from cheap, affordable, safe and diverse food."},{"time":701000,"text":"That's what we must aim for in the next 20 to 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"But yes there are some solutions."},{"time":706000,"text":"And let me just do one simple conceptual thing:"},{"time":710000,"text":"if I plot science as a proxy"},{"time":713000,"text":"for control of the production process and scale."},{"time":717000,"text":"What you see is that we've started"},{"time":719000,"text":"in the left-hand corner with traditional agriculture,"},{"time":722000,"text":"which was sort of small-scale and low-control."},{"time":725000,"text":"We've moved towards large-scale and very high control."},{"time":729000,"text":"What I want us to do is to keep up the science and even get more science in there"},{"time":734000,"text":"but go to a kind of regional scale --"},{"time":736000,"text":"not just in terms of the scale of the fields,"},{"time":738000,"text":"but in terms of the entire food network."},{"time":741000,"text":"That's where we should move."},{"time":743000,"text":"And the ultimate may be, but it doesn't apply to cereals,"},{"time":746000,"text":"that we have entirely closed ecosystems --"},{"time":749000,"text":"the horticultural systems right at the top left-hand corner."},{"time":753000,"text":"So we need to think differently about agriculture science."},{"time":757000,"text":"Agriculture science for most people -- and there are not many farmers"},{"time":759000,"text":"among you here --"},{"time":761000,"text":"has this name of being bad,"},{"time":764000,"text":"of being about pollution, about large-scale,"},{"time":766000,"text":"about the destruction of the environment."},{"time":768000,"text":"That is not necessary."},{"time":770000,"text":"We need more science and not less. And we need good science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773000,"text":"So what kind of science can we have?"},{"time":775000,"text":"Well first of all I think"},{"time":777000,"text":"we can do much better on the existing technologies."},{"time":780000,"text":"Use biotechnology where useful,"},{"time":782000,"text":"particularly in pest and disease resistance."},{"time":785000,"text":"There are also robots, for example,"},{"time":787000,"text":"who can recognize weeds"},{"time":789000,"text":"with a resolution of half an inch."},{"time":792000,"text":"We have much cleverer irrigation."},{"time":794000,"text":"We do not need to spill the water if we don't want to."},{"time":798000,"text":"And we need to think very dispassionately"},{"time":801000,"text":"about the comparative advantages"},{"time":803000,"text":"of small-scale and large-scale."},{"time":806000,"text":"We need to think that land is multi-functional."},{"time":808000,"text":"It has different functions."},{"time":810000,"text":"There are different ways in which we must use it --"},{"time":813000,"text":"for residential, for nature, for agriculture purposes."},{"time":816000,"text":"And we also need to re-examine livestock."},{"time":819000,"text":"Go regional and go to urban food systems."},{"time":822000,"text":"I want to see fish ponds in parking lots and basements."},{"time":826000,"text":"I want to have horticulture"},{"time":828000,"text":"and greenhouses on top of residential areas."},{"time":831000,"text":"And I want to use the energy that comes from those greenhouses"},{"time":834000,"text":"and from the fermentation of crops"},{"time":836000,"text":"to heat our residential areas."},{"time":838000,"text":"There are all kinds of ways we can do it."},{"time":840000,"text":"We cannot solve the world food problem"},{"time":842000,"text":"by using biological agriculture."},{"time":844000,"text":"But we can do a lot more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"And the main thing that I would really ask all of you"},{"time":850000,"text":"as you go back to your countries, or as you stay here:"},{"time":853000,"text":"ask your government for an integrated food policy."},{"time":857000,"text":"Food is as important as energy,"},{"time":860000,"text":"as security, as the environment."},{"time":862000,"text":"Everything is linked together."},{"time":864000,"text":"So we can do that. In fact in a densely populated country"},{"time":867000,"text":"like the River Delta, where I live in the Netherlands,"},{"time":870000,"text":"we have combined these functions."},{"time":872000,"text":"So this is not science fiction. We can combine things"},{"time":875000,"text":"even in a social sense of making"},{"time":877000,"text":"the rural areas more accessible to people --"},{"time":879000,"text":"to house, for example, the chronically sick."},{"time":882000,"text":"There is all kinds of things we can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"But there is something you must do. It's not enough for me to say,"},{"time":887000,"text":"\"Let's get more bold science into agriculture.\""},{"time":890000,"text":"You must go back"},{"time":892000,"text":"and think about your own food chain."},{"time":894000,"text":"Talk to farmers. When was the last time"},{"time":896000,"text":"you went to a farm and talked to a farmer?"},{"time":898000,"text":"Talk to people in restaurants."},{"time":900000,"text":"Understand where you are in the food chain,"},{"time":902000,"text":"where your food comes from."},{"time":904000,"text":"Understand that you are part"},{"time":906000,"text":"of this enormous chain of events."},{"time":908000,"text":"And that frees you up to do other things."},{"time":911000,"text":"And above all, to me, food is about respect."},{"time":915000,"text":"It's about understanding, when you eat,"},{"time":917000,"text":"that there are also many people who are still in this situation,"},{"time":921000,"text":"who are still struggling for their daily food."},{"time":924000,"text":"And the kind of simplistic solutions that we sometimes have,"},{"time":927000,"text":"to think that doing everything by hand"},{"time":929000,"text":"is going to be the solution,"},{"time":931000,"text":"is really not morally justified."},{"time":934000,"text":"We need to help to lift them out of poverty."},{"time":936000,"text":"We need to make them proud of being a farmer"},{"time":940000,"text":"because they allow us to survive."},{"time":943000,"text":"Never before, as I said,"},{"time":945000,"text":"has the responsibility for food"},{"time":947000,"text":"been in the hands of so few."},{"time":949000,"text":"And never before have we had the luxury"},{"time":951000,"text":"of taking it for granted"},{"time":953000,"text":"because it is now so cheap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":956000,"text":"And I think there is nobody else who has expressed"},{"time":958000,"text":"better, to me, the idea that food, in the end,"},{"time":962000,"text":"in our own tradition, is something holy."},{"time":965000,"text":"It's not about nutrients and calories."},{"time":967000,"text":"It's about sharing. It's about honesty. It's about identity."},{"time":971000,"text":"Who said this so beautifully was Mahatma Gandhi,"},{"time":974000,"text":"75 years ago, when he spoke about bread."},{"time":977000,"text":"He did not speak about rice, in India. He said,"},{"time":980000,"text":"\"To those who have to go without two meals a day,"},{"time":984000,"text":"God can only appear as bread.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"And so as I'm finishing my bread here --"},{"time":991000,"text":"and I've been baking it, and I'll try not to burn my hands."},{"time":995000,"text":"Let me share"},{"time":997000,"text":"with those of you here in the first row."},{"time":999000,"text":"Let me share some of the food with you."},{"time":1001000,"text":"Take some of my bread."},{"time":1003000,"text":"And as you eat it, and as you try it --"},{"time":1006000,"text":"please come and stand up."},{"time":1008000,"text":"Have some of it."},{"time":1010000,"text":"I want you to think that every bite connects you"},{"time":1013000,"text":"to the past and the future:"},{"time":1015000,"text":"to these anonymous farmers,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"that first bred the first wheat varieties;"},{"time":1021000,"text":"and to the farmers of today,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"who've been making this. And you don't even know who they are."},{"time":1026000,"text":"Every meal you eat"},{"time":1028000,"text":"contains ingredients from all across the world."},{"time":1032000,"text":"Everything makes us so privileged,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"that we can eat this food, that we don't struggle every day."},{"time":1038000,"text":"And that, I think,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"evolutionarily-speaking is unique."},{"time":1042000,"text":"We've never had that before."},{"time":1044000,"text":"So enjoy your bread."},{"time":1046000,"text":"Eat it, and feel privileged."},{"time":1048000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1050000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}